      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p><p><strong>About The Role</strong></p><p>The Black Tux is transforming the tuxedo and suit rental market. What was a traditional shopping experience is now offered completely online with a focus on quality, fit, and price. We have seen incredible growth since our 2013 launch and are looking for talented engineers to help us as we continue to scale.</p><p>We are looking to hire a growth engineer. You are obsessed with delivering the best possible user experience, value software engineering practices, and enjoy hacking the customer as much as the code.</p><p>You will be joining an engineering team consisting of 6 software engineers, a QA engineer, and a product manager. Our team favors a scrum approach to development. We have a weekly kickoff, a daily standup, and a weekly planning meeting. You will be a critical part of pushing our growth to the next level.</p><p>This is a unique opportunity to be part of an early stage company with a killer product that is backed by Silicon Valley\u2019s top investors.</p><p><strong>What you will do</strong></p><ul>  <li>Build and improve marketing systems for a fast-growing, disruptive e-commerce company</li>  <li>Integrate 3rd party ad delivery, analytics, testing, and tracking platforms</li>    <li>Drive revenue growth through technical initiatives and rapid data-driven iteration</li> <li>Deliver defect limited code through ubiquitous test automation</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul>    <li>3+ years of professional software development</li>  <li>Experience with a dynamic programming language such as Python or Ruby</li>  <li>Familiarity with a web framework: Django, Pyramid, Rails, Node.js, Play, etc.</li>  <li>Fluent in front-end web technologies: HTML, SCSS, JS, jQuery and more</li>  <li>Knowledge of modern web technologies</li>   <li>Experience working in a fast-paced startup environment</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits and Perks of Working at The Black Tux</strong></p><ul>  <li>Exciting startup environment</li>   <li>Weekly catered lunches</li> <li>Dog friendly office</li>    <li>Complimentary dry cleaning &amp; tailoring services</li>    <li>Health, dental and vision coverage</li> <li>Paid Parking</li>   <li>Paid maternity and paternity leave</li> <li>Open vacation time</li> <li>Stocked kitchen &amp; pantry</li>   <li>Apple equipment or whatever you need to be productive</li>  <li>Monthly team outings</li>   <li>Company happy hours</li>    <li>Free suit rentals</li></ul> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/6Q1nj\"/></p>\n",
