      "title":"Big Data Engineer (Java)",
      "location":"Waltham, MA",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>Role \nThe mission of Amadeus\u2019 Hotel IT team is to design and deliver high performance systems that can process tens of thousands of requests per second and return the highest level of accuracy in the fastest response time. Our SaaS platforms are designed to serve millions of users who are seeking information and reservations from tens of thousands of hotels offering millions of hotel rooms around the world. Utilizing our proven ability to build and deploy mission critical software for the global travel industry, we are creating the next generation of technology solutions for the hospitality industry including: reservations and distribution, high-volume data acquisition from heterogeneous sources, sophisticated search engines, payment processing, hotel operations, business intelligence, and revenue management.</p>\n\n<p>The aim of the Hotel Reporting and Business Intelligence team is to provide high volume real-time operational reporting on large systems and novel and revolutionary insights to the hotel industry. We help our customers be become better run and more profitable by improving their level of knowledge about their own businesses and providing actionable data.</p>\n\n<p>The Java Engineer for Reporting and Business Intelligence is an expert on building high availability, high transaction JEE web applications.  </p>\n\n<p>Responsibilities</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build web service oriented web applications to capture, analyze, publish and display data</li>\n<li>Create ETLs to feed the data warehouse </li>\n<li>Create reporting services \nQualifications and Education Requirements</li>\n<li>B.S. or M.S. in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent experience.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated experience working with high availability service oriented applications </li>\n<li>5+ years experience in Java/JEE web development (JBoss, Weblogic, etc.)</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of  SQL (Oracle, MySQL, SQL Server) databases\nPreferred Skills</li>\n<li>Experience with frontend web development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, AngularJS/Ember.js)</li>\n<li>Knowledge of NoSQL (Couchbase, MongoDB)</li>\n<li>Experience with Hadoop (Hive, Pig, Spark, HBase, Impala)</li>\n<li>Experience with Business Intelligence tools (Oracle BI, SSRS) and/or Reporting Tools (JasperReports) a plus</li>\n<li>Experience with stream processing (Kafka, Storm) a plus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Amadeus strives to achieve outstanding results through a diverse workforce. Our employees represent over 123 nationalities. We welcome and embrace individual differences to bring out the brilliance in ourselves, our customers and each other. We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer.</p>\n",
      "how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://career012.successfactors.eu/sfcareer/jobreqcareer?jobId=20001&amp;company=AmadeusProd&amp;username=\">Apply here</a></p>\n",
