      "title":"Airline Ticketing Product Specialist",
      "location":"Tuscon, AZ",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>Basic Function/Scope  -  Under general direction, perform testing and implementation of revenue integrity business rules for ARI\u2019s various products and processes for ARI travel industry customers.  Recommend actions and processes to solve problems, and perform other job related duties as required.\nEssential Functions</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Provide Consultative role as needed.</li>\n<li>Research/correct problems and respond to customer inquiries.</li>\n<li>Work as needed with QA to verify testing is successful for each change request.</li>\n<li>Work directly with Project Management in communicating and supporting customers.</li>\n<li>Create/test/implement business rules (ticketing time limits and other PNR processing rules) within the guidelines and policies of ARI.</li>\n<li>Analyze results and alert customers of any anomalies.</li>\n<li>Provide process and product suggestions to improve ARI\u2019s customer relationships and overall business. </li>\n<li>Analyze customer revenue integrity strategies and propose alternative methods and products.</li>\n<li>Work with assigned Project Manager to manage airline/travel industry accounts.\no   The PM will be the primary contact responsible for active project status, priorities and making sure ARI meets the expected SLA\u2019s.</li>\n<li>Maintain proficiency in multiple Global Distribution Systems.</li>\n<li>Act as a liaison between highly technical ARI staff and specialized airline/travel industry customers.</li>\n<li>Conduct web conferences for ARI clients as needed.<br></li>\n<li>Actively participate in local customer visits to ARI.<br></li>\n<li>Maintain required documentation on the implementation of business rules.</li>\n<li>Completely self sufficient and able to fulfill job requirements with minimal involvement and supervision.<br></li>\n<li>Maintain high levels of professionalism remain positive and embrace change.\nPosition Qualifications</li>\n<li>Bachelor\u2019s or equivalent degree preferred and 1-3 years of experience with more than one airline multi-host system such as AMADEUS, APOLLO, GALILEO, SABRE, SHARES, PARS, etc.</li>\n<li>Recent airline or GDS experience in revenue management, reservations, CRC, airport services or recent travel agent experience.</li>\n<li>Familiarity with office software such as Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.</li>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li>\n<li>Ability to work well with technical staff as well as airline staff.</li>\n<li>Provide on-call customer and ARI technical support as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n",
