      "location":"Santa Monica, CA, US",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p><p><strong>About The Role</strong></p><p>The Black Tux is transforming the tuxedo and suit rental market. What was a traditional shopping experience is now offered completely online with a focus on quality, fit, and price. We have seen incredible growth since our 2013 launch and are looking for talented engineers to help us as we continue to scale.</p><p>As a Quality Assurance Engineer, your primary responsibility will be to ensure the highest standards of excellence and operational coherence in our software systems. You will work alongside product owners, engineers, and customer service to identify risks, validate new functionality, and detect anomalies. This position requires a high attention to detail and a nimble intellect.</p><p>You will be joining an engineering team consisting of 6 software engineers, a QA engineer, and a product manager. Our team favors a scrum approach to development. We have a weekly kickoff, a daily standup, and a weekly planning meeting. We are dedicated to improving the quality of our work and you will be an crucial part of that effort.</p><p>This is a unique opportunity to be part of an early stage company with a killer product that is backed by Silicon Valley\u2019s top investors.</p><p><strong>What you will do</strong></p><ul>    <li>Triage incoming issues and assess potential impact</li> <li>Review functional and design specifications to ensure full understanding of individual deliverables</li>    <li>Identify test requirements from specifications, map test case requirements and design test coverage plans</li>  <li>Develop, document and maintain test artifacts such as functional test cases, data validations, use-cases, negative tests, and exploratory tests</li>    <li>Assume responsibility for release software quality</li> <li>Enhance testing automation</li> <li>Release management</li> <li>Isolate, replicate, and report defects / verify defect fixes</li>   <li>Maintain an encyclopedic knowledge of our applications</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>\u00a0</p><ul>   <li>2+ years of QA technical experience</li>    <li>Knowledge of SDLC in an Agile environment</li>  <li>Familiarity with Linux commands</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits and Perks of Working at The Black Tux</strong></p><ul> <li>Exciting startup environment</li>   <li>Weekly catered lunches</li> <li>Dog friendly office</li>    <li>Complimentary dry cleaning &amp; tailoring services</li>    <li>Health, dental and vision coverage</li> <li>Paid Parking</li>   <li>Paid maternity and paternity leave</li> <li>Open vacation time</li> <li>Stocked kitchen &amp; pantry</li>   <li>Apple equipment or whatever you need to be productive</li>  <li>Monthly team outings</li>   <li>Company happy hours</li>    <li>Free suit rentals</li></ul> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/6PmnP\"/></p>\n",
