      "location":"New York, NY",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>Marketing Engineer\nAd Copy \nNovus is an innovative company that is changing the way the world invests. We are a high growth, disruptive technology firm bringing big data analytics to the alternative investment industry. Our platform enables investors to consistently maximize their performance potential through discovery of true investment acumen and risk, proprietary industry insights and expertise, and effortless data management and enlightenment.</p>\n\n<p>The company is looking for a rock-star developer to lead and build exceptional digital experiences on the Marketing team.</p>\n\n<p>Background</p>\n\n<p>We operate in an industry in which over $120 Trillion is invested annually on behalf pension / endowment / sovereign funds, and private investors / family offices. And yet, the lack of data intelligence and insight results in much of that money being invested based purely on historic track record, with little transparency into performance acumen and / or risk management. This is our challenge and our purpose: to help investors make better investments. And in doing so, we aim to provide the single network on which trusted professionals will engage, promote, and manage their business. In short, we want to help the world invest better. And we need you.</p>\n\n<p>Role</p>\n\n<p>As a Marketing Engineer at Novus, you will be responsible for all things digital on the Marketing team. Your main focus will include the management and improvement of the Novus website. This includes everything from planning redesigns to implementing custom features that improve the sites user-experience. If you\u2019re the right engineer, you\u2019re the type of person that lives and breathes everything dev. related.</p>\n\n<p>In this role, you will oversee all web development projects and be responsible for continuously improving and enhancing the website and the CMS system hosting it. You will also be expected to source and select vendors, suppliers or any freelance talent needed to execute development across various areas.</p>\n\n<p>You will report directly to the VP of Marketing, and be based in New York, NY.</p>\n\n<p>Some of your key responsibilities include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Regularly produce website pages and features to enhance and optimize the overall user-experience of the Novus website </li>\n<li>Ability to hand-code standards-compliant HTML5, JavaScript, and CSS code </li>\n<li>Edit or create HTML emails, web pages and other digital templates to match design specs </li>\n<li>Customize or build features on CMS systems \u2013 preferably Wordpress </li>\n<li>Analyze website behavior, A/B test and optimize to increase conversion rates as well as other engagement metrics </li>\n<li>Provide technical analysis and monitoring of website infrastructure, performance and stability </li>\n<li>Represent a mobile-first mentality and ensure that our sites are as delightful and effective across various mobile devices, platforms and screen sizes </li>\n<li>Collaborate with visual designers and content strategists to solve complex problems with elegant and always on-brand digital solutions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Culture</p>\n\n<p>Our culture is critical to us. It\u2019s how we push ourselves every day to do better than the day before. We expect our team members to deliver on their responsibilities, understand how each and every component of our company works to generate success, and hold themselves and their colleagues accountable to the highest standards. As a result, we will enjoy talking to you if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You have a natural competitive drive to become the best at what you do \u2013 excellence is your top priority in the work you deliver </li>\n<li>You have the ability and proven experience \u2013 demonstrated through your portfolio \u2013 to strategize, plan for and ultimately execute major website design initiatives </li>\n<li>You\u2019re passionate about combining great design and solid code </li>\n<li>You\u2019re a flexible problem-solver who is comfortable in a fast-paced, self-driven environment </li>\n<li>Possesses limitless patience, unflappable focus and a healthy sense of humor </li>\n<li>You value the best answer more than your ego, can remain composed in the heat of the moment, and can critique and vocalize your thoughts while simultaneously building great relationships. Your integrity is non-negotiable </li>\n<li>You are intensely passionate about building great websites. You talk about it, read about it, engage with other developers in the community and think about it constantly \u2013 if you don\u2019t have the fire, you are not right for us </li>\n<li>You are motivated not just by money \u2013 we will build your wealth if you contribute to our journey \u2013 but also by the journey and challenge itself</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Critical Skills / Abilities</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Exceptional HTML, CSS, JAVASCRIPT and PHP coding ability </li>\n<li>Knowledge and understanding of how to deliver exceptional web designs \u2013 including delivering great user experiences </li>\n<li>Strong experience working within content management systems, ideally ones that are Wordpress-based </li>\n<li>Visual design skills are a big plus </li>\n<li>Great communication skills \u2013 able to effectively communicate technical concepts to non-technical individuals </li>\n<li>Understanding SEO/SEM best practices is a plus but not needed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Compensation will be commensurate with the abilities the individual brings to the table, but shall include a competitive base salary, stock options, an unlimited and flexible vacation policy, a comprehensive benefits program (health insurance, corporate gym memberships, perks, 401k etc.), and a robust performance-based incentive pay program.</p>\n",
      "how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"http://grnh.se/p6l4ms\">http://grnh.se/p6l4ms</a></p>\n",
