      "title":"Senior Front-end Developer \u2014 Melbourne",
      "location":"Melbourne, Australia",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>Flippa is looking to hire a senior Ruby developer to join our growing team. We love people who love to learn and share what they learn.</p>\n\n<p>Flippa.com is the world\u2019s largest marketplace for buying and selling digital property (websites, domain names and mobile apps). Born from SitePoint in 2009, we continue to grow, building new features every week and improving our existing platform based on user feedback.</p>\n\n<p>Our development team is based in Collingwood, Melbourne, but we also have an office in San Francisco and we have staff in countries across the globe.</p>\n\n<p>We use Ruby\u2014primarily Ruby on Rails, and JavaScript\u2014a mix of Angular and React\u2014to build our core service and we have a growing number of services written in other languages, such as Node and Go. We are dedicated to automating everything, including our infrastructure. DevOps is a shared responsibility across the team and infrastructure is driven through code. Some technologies we\u2019re using right now are: Ruby, Varnish, Nginx, Docker, Elasticsearch, AWS/CloudFormation, Angular, React, Redis, Sidekiq, Fluxible, WebPack. We allocate time every iteration to pay down technical debt and to improve internal tooling and infrastructure. It\u2019s an exciting place to work and one in which you have the opportunity to experiment and innovate.</p>\n\n<p>As a Senior Developer, you will be responsible for coordinating with our Product and Backend teams to design and build rich front-end applications using React/Angular and Isomorphic JavaScript in order to facilitate our growth into new areas.</p>\n\n<p>Once every 3 months we take a couple of days out from regular business and get together to hack on cool things proposed by our team, just for the fun of it. Our office is shared by SitePoint, Learnable, Influx and PromisePay, so there are plenty of technical people around to talk code with. We run \u201cDev Lunch\u201d sessions once every 2 weeks, in which we nom our way though many boxes of pizza and anybody is invited to get up and present something they think the team could find interesting.</p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re looking for the following skills:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with Angular and/or React</li>\n<li>Good sense of UX and design</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of CSS and CSS frameworks</li>\n<li>ES6</li>\n<li>Broad knowledge of the rapidly changing JavaScript landscape</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Bonus points for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>An active GitHub profile</li>\n<li>Experience with Flux</li>\n<li>Docker</li>\n<li>Elasticsearch experience</li>\n<li>Service Oriented Architecture experience</li>\n<li>AWS development experience</li>\n</ul>\n",
      "how_to_apply":"<p>Interested applicants should send a CV and/or active GitHub profile to <a href=\"mailto:devjobs@flippa.com\">devjobs@flippa.com</a>, along with a short introduction about yourself and the subject line &quot;I love building Internet&quot; to show that you have read this job description.</p>\n",
