      "description":"<p>We are looking for a highly motivated and talented technical individual to join our team as a DevOps Engineer. The ideal candidate has 2+ years of demonstrated ability to successfully manage infrastructure by using automation, programming and systems management.</p>\n\n<p>Responsibilities</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Maintaining and improving the systems infrastructure and application development platform for a leading global destination and platform for Japanese anime and Asian content</li>\n<li>Perform oncall duties supporting the production environment</li>\n<li>Improving and automating oncall responsibilities to reduce oncall noise</li>\n<li>Extending Puppet through Ruby, Hiera, custom facts, and writing collective extensions</li>\n<li>Implmenting and working with tools similar defined below</li>\n<li>Identifying and analyzing problems in the environment and design, build and/or configure new tools or solutions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Requirements</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Strong background (2+ years) in Linux systems administration, specifically RHEL/CentOS</li>\n<li>Strong programming background and analytical skills</li>\n<li>Experience with managing and configuring DNS servers (BIND, TinyDNS)</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to understand complex systems, and drilling down to resolve problems.</li>\n<li>Experience maintaining Puppet</li>\n<li>Experience supporting the LAMP stack</li>\n<li>Experience with deployments and resolving issues quickly</li>\n<li>Familiar with monitoring and graphing systems (Nagios/Icinga, Cacti, Ganglia, Graphite) to ensure 100% up time</li>\n<li>Experience with cloud and virtualization platforms like VMWare, Xen, Hyper-V, Openstack is a plus</li>\n<li>Understanding of networking technologies (Load Balancers, Firewalls, Switches, etc) is a plus</li>\n<li>Experience with cloud based hosting, specifically AWS is a plus</li>\n<li>Experience with the Ruby language is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive salary</li>\n<li>Health, dental and vision insurance, 401k, and Commuter benefits</li>\n<li>Fun, passionate and skilled co-workers</li>\n<li>Free lunches 4x/week</li>\n<li>Pet friendly environment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>About Crunchyroll, Inc.</p>\n\n<p>Crunchyroll is a leading global destination and platform for Japanese anime and Asian content. Through applications including Crunchyroll for iPhone, iPad, Android, Playstation\u00ae3, Playstation\u00ae4, Xbox LIVE\u00ae, AppleTV, Roku, Internet-enabled TVs, set-top boxes, affiliate websites and its own streaming website, Crunchyroll delivers more than 25,000 episodes and 15,000 hours of officially-licensed content from leading Asian media producers direct to viewers translated professionally in multiple languages within minutes of TV broadcast.  The company is profitable, and has over 400,000 paid subscribers.</p>\n\n<p>Crunchyroll was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in San Francisco.  Desired candidate will be a part of an exciting initiative that will directly interact with Crunchyroll and other channel initiatives such as Soompi TV, and Creativebug, but will be an independent platform offering, which is backed by OTT Media, AT&amp;T and The Chernin Group.</p>\n\n<p>About Otter Media</p>\n\n<p>AT&amp;T and The Chernin Group formed Otter Media in April 2014 to acquire, invest in and launch global over-the-top (OTT) video services. With more than $500 million in funding committed to the venture, the alliance positions both companies to take advantage of the rapid growth of online video services, with each party bringing significant and complementary strengths. One of the strategic focuses of the venture is to invest in and build advertising and OTT video services for targeted audiences.</p>\n\n<p>Otter Media&#39;s portfolio includes a majority stake in Crunchyroll, a leading global subscription and ad-supported video platform for Japanese anime and Korean content, and Creativebug, one of the top go-to sources for high-quality online video arts and crafts instruction.</p>\n",
