      "location":"San Francisco, CA",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>We believe in teamwork, communication, trust and not taking ourselves too seriously. We believe in the power of small teams. We believe in supporting personal growth and the importance of nurturing a great culture.</p>\n\n<p>The Rewards Team, is the engine behind Rally\u2019s incentive program for doing healthy stuff throughout your day. Simple activities such as eating better, taking the steps instead of the elevator and getting routine checkups earns you coins &amp; rewards. You can then exchange these coins &amp; rewards for gift cards or lower your insurance payments!</p>\n\n<p><strong>About us:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Flexible minds: We need to do a lot with a small team, so it&#39;s important to use the right tools for the right job and be willing to change down the line if we find a more efficient solution. We also believe in &quot;strong opinions, weakly held,&quot; being humble, accepting and giving feedback.</li>\n<li>Self-driven: Developers are given a large amount of autonomy in how they work, who they work with, when they work, and are responsible for a large part of driving project functionality and seeing them through to completion.</li>\n<li>Quality-focused: Quality code helps a small team do more. Increasing communication through code readability decreases the cost of maintenance to ensure we don&#39;t work weekends.</li>\n<li>Entrepreneurial: Developers are given complete ownership over their projects from design to implementation, testing, deployment and production maintenance.</li>\n<li>Communicative: We believe in teamwork and sharing the experience through design reviews, code reviews and weekly technology presentations.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About you:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Architect, build and ship highly scalable systems, libraries, and frameworks</li>\n<li>Write code using primarily Scala</li>\n<li>Strong Java Background - Expert Level Design &amp; Development.</li>\n<li>Exposure to or Strong Desire to Learn Scala.</li>\n<li>Strong Unit Testing Experience (prefer Scalatest/Spec2/ScalaCheck).</li>\n<li>Commercial Experience with Distributed, High-Performance Systems.</li>\n<li>Database Experience (Postgres or MongoDB a plus).</li>\n<li>Cloud based services and hosting (AWS EC2, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience integrating with third party API\u2019s</li>\n<li>Developing APIs and Web Services</li>\n<li>Open source projects</li>\n<li>Comfort with Git</li>\n<li>Exposure to JavaScript based framework like AngularJS/Coffee script</li>\n<li>6+ years of real industry experience</li>\n<li>B.S. degree (preferred)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment-qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records</p>\n",
