      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>JW Player is looking for a talented full-stack Software Engineer to join Portal team in our New York City headquarters. As a member of the Portal Team, you will be joining a small, collaborative team responsible for our internal and user-facing dashboards, our eCommerce and direct-sold payments systems, and our internal user account management APIs. This role will report to the Lead Software Engineer on the Portal Team.</p>\n\n<p>In this role, you will:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work as part of a scrum team in an agile environment </li>\n<li>Build and maintain the Platform architecture, from our static Angular frontend through to our RESTful Python API </li>\n<li>Develop new commercial features from our Product Backlog </li>\n<li>Prototype new ideas and explore new solutions to the growing list of challenges the Platform team is responsible for</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Requirements</p>\n\n<p>2+ years of experience as a Software Engineer \nExpert-level understanding of Python and JavaScript \nStrong relational database skills (MySQL a plus) \nSmart, and able to get things done \nBS in Computer Science or related field</p>\n\n<p>Bonus Points</p>\n\n<p>Experience with data-binding JavaScript frameworks (we use Angular.js) \nFamiliarity building eCommerce platforms \nComfortable in a fast-paced Agile environment \nContinuous delivery, test automation</p>\n",
