      "title":"Android Mobile Developer",
      "location":"Boston, MA",
      "type":"Full Time",
      "description":"<p>Company Description</p>\n\n<p>Who We Are</p>\n\n<p>Founded by industry veterans Drs. Ido and Roy Schoenberg, American Well\u2019s mission is to improve access to quality care and make it more affordable and transparent for consumers. We do this by using mobile and web technology to remove barriers such as distance, mobility, and time.</p>\n\n<p>What We Do</p>\n\n<p>American Well offers software, services, and access to clinical services \u2013 everything you need to offer a complete telehealth service \u2013 whether you are a health plan, an employer, or a delivery network. Our mobile and web service connects doctors with patients for live, on-demand video visits over the internet and handles all the administration, security, and record keeping that modern healthcare requires.</p>\n\n<p>Job Description</p>\n\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Design, implement and maintain android applications using REST web services</li>\n<li>Responsible for architecting, developing, and supporting American Well\u2019s Android Telehealth product</li>\n<li>Conducts analysis of organizational needs and goals for the development and implementation of the product</li>\n<li>Able to work independently on compressed schedules in a fast paced environment to meet demand.</li>\n<li>Recognizes process or programming inefficiencies, and recommends improvements.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n\n<p>Skills:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 2 years experience building mobile apps using the Android SDK,\nsome knowledge of the Android NDK would be a plus.</li>\n<li>BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent.</li>\n<li>Experience in mobile interface design and development</li>\n<li>Experience completing an application and seeing it through full life cycle of development</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Additional Information</p>\n\n<p>American Well is shaking up the healthcare industry by paving the way for telehealth \u2013 on-demand appointments with doctors and specialists through your phone , tablet or kiosk.  Our app \u2013 Amwell \u2013 was the most popular telehealth app of 2014 with more than 1 million downloads to date, and we recently raised $81 million in Series C funding.  We are an innovation-driven culture poised for exponential growth. Our remarkable growth in 2014 has been a precursor for even more growth in 2015 and the years beyond.</p>\n\n<p>American Well is located in Boston, downtown in the 75 State Street building on the 26th floor. We are 5 min walking from both North and South Station so your commute should be easy! American Well has an amazing culture and we pride ourselves on working hard but creating a fun, energetic environment. </p>\n\n<p>What American Well can offer you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>An opportunity to have a major impact on the future direction of our technology </li>\n<li>3 weeks\u2019 vacation</li>\n<li>401K</li>\n<li>Amazing health, dental and vision insurance plans</li>\n<li>Free gym access - without ever leaving the building </li>\n<li>Drop-off/pick up dry cleaning service</li>\n<li>Beautiful office/work space with views overlooking all of Boston</li>\n<li>A great location in the heart of the financial district</li>\n<li>A well-stocked fridge</li>\n</ul>\n",
      "how_to_apply":"<p>Please APPLY ONLINE at: <a href=\"https://www.smartrecruiters.com/AmericanWell/83949099-android-mobile-developer\">https://www.smartrecruiters.com/AmericanWell/83949099-android-mobile-developer</a></p>\n",
